<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"><Name>06_cv_steward</Name><NextEntryID>175</NextEntryID><EntryCount>174</EntryCount><Entries><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"I felt Maerwald's passing. You slew him?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"I felt Maerwald's passing. You slew him?"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"It is good to see you here, my lord. I can feel a change in the air already. There is much to do." 

"Is there anything I can do to help? </DefaultText><FemaleText>"It is good to see you here, my lord. I can feel a change in the air already. There is much to do." 

"Is there anything I can do to help? </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"What does being the master of Caed Nua entail?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"What does being the master of Caed Nua entail?"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Why, there are many responsibilities involved in maintaining a keep... The extent to which you wish to get involved is entirely up to you, of course. Part of the reason I am here is to ensure that things run smoothly in your absence - provided we have been given instruction." </DefaultText><FemaleText>"Why, there are many responsibilities involved in maintaining a keep... The extent to which you wish to get involved is entirely up to you, of course. Part of the reason I am here is to ensure that things run smoothly in your absence - provided we have been given instruction." </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"What did you mean by 'risks'?" </DefaultText><FemaleText>"What did you mean by 'risks'?" </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Every effort to settle here has failed - from the time of our Aedyran colonists onward. Beasts rise from the Endless Paths, until the new lord or lady is no more. The one who dwells below, this... 'Master', does not tolerate rivals, it seems. I have seen, from time to time, intrepid explorers descend to lay claim to what answers they can... but none return.

"This is the force which has kept Caed Nua a barren ruin... and robbed me of my hopes."

</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Every effort to settle here has failed - from the time of our Aedyran colonists onward. Beasts rise from the Endless Paths, until the new lord or lady is no more. The one who dwells below, this... 'Master', does not tolerate rivals, it seems. I have seen, from time to time, intrepid explorers descend to lay claim to what answers they can... but none return.

"This is the force which has kept Caed Nua a barren ruin... and robbed me of my hopes."

</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"What are the Endless Paths?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"What are the Endless Paths?"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Who is this Master Below?" </DefaultText><FemaleText>"Who is this Master Below?" </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"But am I not the master of Caed Nua?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"But am I not the master of Caed Nua?"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"The Endless Paths of Od Nua. That is the name given to the labyrinth beneath the keep. The erl, he... We were warned, by the Glanfathans, that this site was cursed. And there is a legend attached to it, though at the time we thought nothing of it." </DefaultText><FemaleText>"The Endless Paths of Od Nua. That is the name given to the labyrinth beneath the keep. The erl, he... We were warned, by the Glanfathans, that this site was cursed. And there is a legend attached to it, though at the time we thought nothing of it." </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"No one living knows how far down the tunnels stretch, and few who have ventured there have returned. There is much talk of riches and treasure... the promise of Engwithan relics alone has drawn many fortune-seekers. To their deaths, I fear." </DefaultText><FemaleText>"No one living knows how far down the tunnels stretch, and few who have ventured there have returned. There is much talk of riches and treasure... the promise of Engwithan relics alone has drawn many fortune-seekers. To their deaths, I fear." </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"I cannot imagine much remains of his work, for the ruins have been here a thousand years or more. But what is left is... impressive. The erl certainly thought so." </DefaultText><FemaleText>"I cannot imagine much remains of his work, for the ruins have been here a thousand years or more. But what is left is... impressive. The erl certainly thought so." </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Then I shall seek out and defeat this 'Master Below'."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Then I shall seek out and defeat this 'Master Below'."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"But should you succeed, your name will be known across the Dyrwood. You will be sole master of Caed Nua, and the restoration of its great name. And I would remember you for it, my lord, for so long as a single stone remains of Caed Nua." </DefaultText><FemaleText>"But should you succeed, your name will be known across the Dyrwood. You will be sole master of Caed Nua, and the restoration of its great name. And I would remember you for it, my lord, for so long as a single stone remains of Caed Nua." </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>[Leave] "Time to find this 'queen' in the 'city of defiance'." </DefaultText><FemaleText>[Leave] "Time to find this 'queen' in the 'city of defiance'." </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"I could... make arrangements to have it repaired, if it is your will. When it ceased to be the previous master's will, I became powerless to do anything about it, for what am I but the master's instrument? 

"It would take time, but far less than finding another route to Defiance Bay."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"I could... make arrangements to have it repaired, if it is your will. When it ceased to be the previous master's will, I became powerless to do anything about it, for what am I but the master's instrument? 

"It would take time, but far less than finding another route to Defiance Bay."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"What is the state of the keep?" </DefaultText><FemaleText>"What is the state of the keep?" </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Ah, where to begin? Let's see here..." </DefaultText><FemaleText>"Ah, where to begin? Let's see here..." </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>As you come to the end of the great hall, you perceive an inviting warmth radiating from a grand throne wrought out of marble, its masterful artistry out of place amidst the castle's more practical stonework. The veiled face of a woman is carved above the throne's backing, watching over the room with hollow eyes.

At your approach, you feel the warmth fluctuate, as though stirring. A voice rings out from the carving, permeating the fortress through stone and air.</DefaultText><FemaleText>As you come to the end of the great hall, you perceive an inviting warmth radiating from a grand throne wrought out of marble, its masterful artistry out of place amidst the castle's more practical stonework. The veiled face of a woman is carved above the throne's backing, watching over the room with hollow eyes.

At your approach, you feel the warmth fluctuate, as though stirring. A voice rings out from the carving, permeating the fortress through stone and air.</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"As am I. If you should happen to find him, I would be glad to know of it. Each day his absence brings new dust to my halls, new cracks to my stones. It's- it's shameful is what it is. The erl would never have let it come to this.

"You are free to search for him here. I will unbar the way."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"As am I. If you should happen to find him, I would be glad to know of it. Each day his absence brings new dust to my halls, new cracks to my stones. It's- it's shameful is what it is. The erl would never have let it come to this.

"You are free to search for him here. I will unbar the way."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"You said these were your halls?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"You said these were your halls?"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Not as a land is its lord's. More... as a child is its mother's. This castle was my design, you see. The erl appointed me to do it. I was... getting on in years. I knew it would be my only chance to build something magnificent."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Not as a land is its lord's. More... as a child is its mother's. This castle was my design, you see. The erl appointed me to do it. I was... getting on in years. I knew it would be my only chance to build something magnificent."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Tell me more about Maerwald."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Tell me more about Maerwald."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"He was a great man. He came here one day, young with long hair and polished armor, and he banished the dark things that had come to lurk in this place after centuries of neglect.
 
"He could see the beauty of this place. The way it had been. So he claimed it for his own when no one else would take it. We worked together to restore it."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"He was a great man. He came here one day, young with long hair and polished armor, and he banished the dark things that had come to lurk in this place after centuries of neglect.
 
"He could see the beauty of this place. The way it had been. So he claimed it for his own when no one else would take it. We worked together to restore it."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Any idea where I can find Maerwald?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Any idea where I can find Maerwald?"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"I can feel his presence faintly somewhere deeper inside the keep. But he uses his gifts to confound me, and my senses are dulled while he does so. I only wish I could know his mind."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"I can feel his presence faintly somewhere deeper inside the keep. But he uses his gifts to confound me, and my senses are dulled while he does so. I only wish I could know his mind."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"خداحافظ."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"خداحافظ."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"The Watcher returns. Well, one of them, at least. Have you had any luck finding Maerwald?" </DefaultText><FemaleText>"The Watcher returns. Well, one of them, at least. Have you had any luck finding Maerwald?" </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>The energy seems all at once to drain from the air. "I see.

"If it's Defiance Bay you seek, I'm sorry to tell you that you've come a long way for nothing. The Eastern Barbican collapsed decades ago, and Maerwald never got around to rebuilding it. The road here is a dead end. He got as far as gathering materials before his mind became... preoccupied."</DefaultText><FemaleText>The energy seems all at once to drain from the air. "I see.

"If it's Defiance Bay you seek, I'm sorry to tell you that you've come a long way for nothing. The Eastern Barbican collapsed decades ago, and Maerwald never got around to rebuilding it. The road here is a dead end. He got as far as gathering materials before his mind became... preoccupied."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"How do I repair the barbican?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"How do I repair the barbican?"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Maerwald set aside materials for the barbican, and they are still available to you. In the future, if you wish to make further repairs to the keep, we will need coin for supplies and labor."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Maerwald set aside materials for the barbican, and they are still available to you. In the future, if you wish to make further repairs to the keep, we will need coin for supplies and labor."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Maerwald kept a ledger, as it happens, and I have taken the liberty of updating it... You could take a look, if you wish?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Maerwald kept a ledger, as it happens, and I have taken the liberty of updating it... You could take a look, if you wish?"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"سوالات دیگری دارم."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"سوالات دیگری دارم."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Yes? How can I help?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Yes? How can I help?"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"You - you've done it. I felt the change from here. It's as if there was a noise - a voice, underlying every sound in the keep, and I had simply ceased to notice... The silence now seems almost strange."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"You - you've done it. I felt the change from here. It's as if there was a noise - a voice, underlying every sound in the keep, and I had simply ceased to notice... The silence now seems almost strange."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"My lord, you seem to have received a letter. From a rather unpleasant messenger, I have to say. Still, I have it here, and I can relay the contents to you if you wish."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"My lord, you seem to have received a letter. From a rather unpleasant messenger, I have to say. Still, I have it here, and I can relay the contents to you if you wish."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"What did the messenger want?" </DefaultText><FemaleText>"What did the messenger want?" </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"I can't be troubled with this right now." </DefaultText><FemaleText>"I can't be troubled with this right now." </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"To issue a challenge, it seems. Not his own, but on behalf of his lord. It seems you've made an enemy, I'm afraid. This Lord Raedric seems to be very angry with you." 

"He demands that you face him at his keep, and has threatened to attack Caed Nua until you do so. He has a touch of the dramatic in him, I have to say." </DefaultText><FemaleText>"To issue a challenge, it seems. Not his own, but on behalf of his lord. It seems you've made an enemy, I'm afraid. This Lord Raedric seems to be very angry with you." 

"He demands that you face him at his keep, and has threatened to attack Caed Nua until you do so. He has a touch of the dramatic in him, I have to say." </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"About that mysterious missive..."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"About that mysterious missive..."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Oh, yes - would you like me to relay the message now?" </DefaultText><FemaleText>"Oh, yes - would you like me to relay the message now?" </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Of course, of course. Another time, then."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Of course, of course. Another time, then."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Another Watcher in Caed Nua. Glowing very brightly indeed to these eyes. What strange happenstance."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Another Watcher in Caed Nua. Glowing very brightly indeed to these eyes. What strange happenstance."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"I'm looking for Maerwald."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"I'm looking for Maerwald."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"What erl were you speaking of?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"What erl were you speaking of?"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Are you imprisoned in that throne?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Are you imprisoned in that throne?"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"When it was built I couldn't bring myself to part from it. To go back to my lonely home. I begged the erl to let me stay, to take care of it. It was all I wanted, and he granted it.

"Years later, when Berath's Usher finally came calling, I begged the erl to find a way to let me remain. And so he did."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"When it was built I couldn't bring myself to part from it. To go back to my lonely home. I begged the erl to let me stay, to take care of it. It was all I wanted, and he granted it.

"Years later, when Berath's Usher finally came calling, I begged the erl to find a way to let me remain. And so he did."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"But he began to grow distant some time ago. He never told me why. He retreated deeper and deeper into the keep, never leaving, sending servants for food, hiding himself from my sight. The restorations stopped." The voice gives a wistful sigh.

"Now to look at the place, you'd never know the progress we'd made. In most places it's worse than it ever was. And all I can do is watch it crumble around me."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"But he began to grow distant some time ago. He never told me why. He retreated deeper and deeper into the keep, never leaving, sending servants for food, hiding himself from my sight. The restorations stopped." The voice gives a wistful sigh.

"Now to look at the place, you'd never know the progress we'd made. In most places it's worse than it ever was. And all I can do is watch it crumble around me."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"The Erl of Yenwood. The original, in fact, when Dyrwood was a colony. He found this site, the only ruin Eir Glanfath refused to defend, and he believed its wealth would be great. The keep was his way of defending his family's claim, and that claim became his obsession. He had to know what lay beneath."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"The Erl of Yenwood. The original, in fact, when Dyrwood was a colony. He found this site, the only ruin Eir Glanfath refused to defend, and he believed its wealth would be great. The keep was his way of defending his family's claim, and that claim became his obsession. He had to know what lay beneath."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Imprisoned? At times it feels that way, I suppose. But it's more that I reside here.

"The throne was brought up from the ruins. One of the first things they found. As a last favor to a dying woman, the erl arranged for me to be moved into it. Adra is an accommodating vessel for a soul."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Imprisoned? At times it feels that way, I suppose. But it's more that I reside here.

"The throne was brought up from the ruins. One of the first things they found. As a last favor to a dying woman, the erl arranged for me to be moved into it. Adra is an accommodating vessel for a soul."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"He devoted his life to excavating the ruins below the keep. They had been sealed with rock and soil. Deliberately, it would seem."

"Years passed, and with them the erl. He dug his entire life and never found what he sought. His obsession became his son's, and his son's son's. And one day, that young erl broke through."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"He devoted his life to excavating the ruins below the keep. They had been sealed with rock and soil. Deliberately, it would seem."

"Years passed, and with them the erl. He dug his entire life and never found what he sought. His obsession became his son's, and his son's son's. And one day, that young erl broke through."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"What did he find?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"What did he find?"</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"I'd like to ask you something else."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"I'd like to ask you something else."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"An endless maze, incomprehensible in its construction. But he would never come to learn more than that. Vile things had taken residence there. Vile and dangerous. They poured up through the keep and slew its residents, the erl among them."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"An endless maze, incomprehensible in its construction. But he would never come to learn more than that. Vile things had taken residence there. Vile and dangerous. They poured up through the keep and slew its residents, the erl among them."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"After that the keep remained abandoned. Unused. Wasted. Maerwald's mastery of this place was the first hope I'd had in two hundred years. How I've longed to see it as it once was."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"After that the keep remained abandoned. Unused. Wasted. Maerwald's mastery of this place was the first hope I'd had in two hundred years. How I've longed to see it as it once was."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Oh it's not as confining as it seems. I can feel the whole keep from here, and all things that are tied to it. There's something about this throne and its construction. Or maybe it's something about this place."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Oh it's not as confining as it seems. I can feel the whole keep from here, and all things that are tied to it. There's something about this throne and its construction. Or maybe it's something about this place."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"I can only guess why this all has happened. I fear I've wronged the gods, putting this place here, and they've doomed me to watch it wear away into dust. To witness my own folly."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"I can only guess why this all has happened. I fear I've wronged the gods, putting this place here, and they've doomed me to watch it wear away into dust. To witness my own folly."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"He gave me no choice."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"He gave me no choice."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"The old fool was barking mad. I did him a favor."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"The old fool was barking mad. I did him a favor."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Several of him."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Several of him."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>The steward is silent a moment. The air seems to chill.

"It saddens me to hear it. But part of me is grateful to no longer have to wait and worry in darkness."</DefaultText><FemaleText>The steward is silent a moment. The air seems to chill.

"It saddens me to hear it. But part of me is grateful to no longer have to wait and worry in darkness."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"This place has always known its master, long as it's had one. It has a will all its own, which has little to do with the castle and much to do with the land it's built on. It looks to you as Maerwald's successor now, whether you care for it or not.

"A dubious honor, inheriting a fortress both broken and cursed. But in the right hands it could be so much more! If you had only seen it in its day.

"Will you- will you stay?"</DefaultText><FemaleText>"This place has always known its master, long as it's had one. It has a will all its own, which has little to do with the castle and much to do with the land it's built on. It looks to you as Maerwald's successor now, whether you care for it or not.

"A dubious honor, inheriting a fortress both broken and cursed. But in the right hands it could be so much more! If you had only seen it in its day.

