emaleText>"Was this your keep, once?" </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Not as a land is its lord's. More... as a child is its mother's. This castle was my design, you see. The erl appointed me to do it. I was... getting on in years. I knew it would be my only chance to build something magnificent."</DefaultText><FemaleText>"Not as a land is its lord's. More... as a child is its mother's. This castle was my design, you see. The erl appointed me to do it. I was... getting on in years. I knew it would be my only chance to build something magnificent."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"When it was built I couldn't bring myself to part from it. To go back to my lonely home. I begged the erl to let me stay, to take care of it. It was all I wanted, and he granted it.

