nto dust. To witness my own folly."</FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Certainly. What would you like to know?" </DefaultText><FemaleText>"Certainly. What would you like to know?" </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Now it has a new master, and a second chance....As do I." </DefaultText><FemaleText>"Now it has a new master, and a second chance....As do I." </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Yes. An endless maze, incomprehensible in its construction. But he would never come to learn more than that. Vile things had taken residence there. Vile and dangerous. They poured up through the keep and slew its residents, the erl among them." </DefaultText><FemaleText>"Yes. An endless maze, incomprehensible in its construction. But he would never come to learn more than that. Vile things had taken residence there. Vile and dangerous. They poured up through the keep and slew its residents, the erl among them." </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"You have avenged those deaths, and I thank you for it. I can only hope their souls have found peace, or else new lives, out in the world somewhere." </DefaultText><FemaleText>"You have avenged those deaths, and I thank you for it. I can only hope their souls have found peace, or else new lives, out in the world somewhere." </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"After the attack, the keep remained abandoned for two hundred years. When Maerwald arrived, I hoped that I might finally see the keep restored." </DefaultText><FemaleText>"After the attack, the keep remained abandoned for two hundred years. When Maerwald arrived, I hoped that I might finally see the keep restored." </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"It seems I was mistaken - for you have been the salvation of this place, not he. I thought the curse upon this place would never fall. That I would watch the very stones wear away into dust." </DefaultText><FemaleText>"It seems I was mistaken - for you have been the salvation of this place, not he. I thought the curse upon this place would never fall. That I would watch the very stones wear away into dust." </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"In restoring the keep... my great design... you have restored my purpose. Your name, your soul, is writ upon the very stone. I know Caed Nua will not fall again." </DefaultText><FemaleText>"In restoring the keep... my great design... you have restored my purpose. Your name, your soul, is writ upon the very stone. I know Caed Nua will not fall again." </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Are you imprisoned in that throne?" </DefaultText><FemaleText>"Are you imprisoned in that throne?" </FemaleText></Entry><Entry ID=""><DefaultText>"Imprisoned? At times it feels that way, I suppose. But it's more that I reside here.

